\"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Gregory_I\"}, {\"begin\": 2385, \"end\": 2387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999956165475518, \"rank\": 4.383035689338891e-06, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"AP\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2336}, {\"ngram\": \"their days\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2357}, {\"ngram\": \"onTahiti\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"fishers\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"their catches\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"the fish\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With fishing being a vital part of the ways of Polynesian life, local leader Dominique Tehei, 51, and his fellow community members knew they needed to find a way to restore the ecosystem.\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2715, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999998299799844, \"rank\": 9.329318359448296e-08, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fishing\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"a vital part\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"the ways\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2571}, {\"ngram\": \"local leader Dominique Tehei\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2620}, {\"ngram\": \"his fellow community members\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2658}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"the ecosystem\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They decided there was a customary Polynesian practice that could help them do it: creating a rahui.\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2751, \"end\": 2761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999998299799844, \"rank\": 9.329318359448296e-08, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rahui\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The traditional conservation method of regulating human activity to help replenish and protect maritime ecosystems resources is being revived and showing results in Tahiti, including the area nearthe Paris Olympics surfing venue.While local communities and leaders acknowledge that rahui are not a one-stop solution to all environmental issues, they are working with researchers and scientists to help strengthen the ground-up, community-based approach.\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.999998344794227, \"rank\": 1.6552086216739654e-06, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 3018, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The traditional conservation method\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2853}, {\"ngram\": \"human activity\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2882}, {\"ngram\": \"maritime\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 2921}, {\"ngram\": \"resources\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 2942}, {\"ngram\": \"results\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2979}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 3001, \"to\": 3009}, {\"ngram\": \"venue\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3046}, {\"ngram\": \"local communities\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3070}, {\"ngram\": \"leaders\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3082}, {\"ngram\": \"rahui\", \"from\": 3100, \"to\": 3105}, {\"ngram\": \"a one-stop solution\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3133}, {\"ngram\": \"all environmental issues\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3161}, {\"ngram\": \"researchers\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3196}, {\"ngram\": \"scientists\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3211}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground-up\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \", community-based approach\", \"from\": 3244, \"to\": 3270}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For centuries, rahui have been implemented in the French Polynesian islands, Hawaii and New Zealand, temporarily banning or restricting the harvesting of natural resources in designated areas, said Hunter Lenihan, an ecologist and co-director of the Rahui Forum and Resource Center headquartered in Moorea, Tahiti.\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3323, \"end\": 3329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8693370530247003, \"rank\": 0.14832326835790846, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3330, \"end\": 3340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9999998299799844, \"rank\": 9.329318359448296e-08, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 3350, \"end\": 3356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999999997635314, \"rank\": 2.3643764569016183e-10, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}, {\"begin\": 3361, \"end\": 3372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.824104871345789, \"rank\": 0.20628436673972772, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3471, \"end\": 3477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Region\", \"score\": 0.9750024343173254, \"rank\": 0.022997667047065382, \"text\": \"Hunter\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Region\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Region\"}, {\"begin\": 3580, \"end\": 3586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.999998344794227, \"rank\": 1.6552086216739654e-06, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"centuries\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3286}, {\"ngram\": \"rahui\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3293}, {\"ngram\": \"the harvesting\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3423}, {\"ngram\": \"natural resources\", \"from\": 3427, \"to\": 3444}, {\"ngram\": \"designated areas\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3464}, {\"ngram\": \"an ecologist and co-director\", \"from\": 3487, \"to\": 3515}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rahui Forum and Resource Center\", \"from\": 3519, \"to\": 3554}, {\"ngram\": \"Moorea\", \"from\": 3572, \"to\": 3578}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"(The practice) was squashed by colonizers,\\\" said Lenihan, \\\"but ... is going through a revival that began intensively about a decade ago.\\\"\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3727, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The practice\", \"from\": 3591, \"to\": 3603}, {\"ngram\": \"colonizers\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3631}, {\"ngram\": \"Lenihan\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3646}, {\"ngram\": \"a revival\", \"from\": 3674, \"to\": 3683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the most common form of rahui is a no-fishing zone placed in a lagoon or offshore - like a marine reserve - rahui have also been established in local creeks and rivers in the form of planting taro crops to capture sediment from agriculture or other development before it flows into the ocean and harmfully settles onto reefs.\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 4060, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most common form\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3755}, {\"ngram\": \"rahui\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3764}, {\"ngram\": \"a no-fishing zone\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3785}, {\"ngram\": \"a lagoon\", \"from\": 3796, \"to\": 3804}, {\"ngram\": \"a marine reserve - rahui\", \"from\": 3824, \"to\": 3848}, {\"ngram\": \"local creeks\", \"from\": 3879, \"to\": 3891}, {\"ngram\": \"rivers\", \"from\": 3896, \"to\": 3902}, {\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 3906, \"to\": 3914}, {\"ngram\": \"planting taro crops\", \"from\": 3918, \"to\": 3937}, {\"ngram\": \"sediment\", \"from\": 3949, \"to\": 3957}, {\"ngram\": \"agriculture\", \"from\": 3963, \"to\": 3974}, {\"ngram\": \"other development\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3995}, {\"ngram\": \"the ocean\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4026}, {\"ngram\": \"reefs\", \"from\": 4054, \"to\": 4059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even in the no-fishing zones, rules can vary based on the area's needs.\", \"from\": 4064, \"to\": 4135, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the no-fishing zones\", \"from\": 4072, \"to\": 4092}, {\"ngram\": \"rules\", \"from\": 4094, \"to\": 4099}, {\"ngram\": \"the area's needs\", \"from\": 4118, \"to\": 4134}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes, fishing is only permitted during a certain season.\", \"from\": 4136, \"to\": 4197, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fishing\", \"from\": 4147, \"to\": 4154}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain season\", \"from\": 4180, \"to\": 4196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other times, only certain methods like line or spear fishing are permitted, forbidding the use of nets or cages.\", \"from\": 4198, \"to\": 4310, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only certain methods\", \"from\": 4211, \"to\": 4231}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4241}, {\"ngram\": \"spear fishing\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4258}, {\"ngram\": \"the use\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4292}, {\"ngram\": \"nets\", \"from\": 4296, \"to\": 4300}, {\"ngram\": \"cages\", \"from\": 4304, \"to\": 4309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In some rahui, fishing and swimming is prohibited entirely, protecting some areas from tourism overdevelopment.\", \"from\": 4311, \"to\": 4422, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some rahui\", \"from\": 4314, \"to\": 4324}, {\"ngram\": \"fishing\", \"from\": 4326, \"to\": 4333}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 4338, \"to\": 4346}, {\"ngram\": \"some areas\", \"from\": 4382, \"to\": 4392}, {\"ngram\": \"tourism overdevelopment\", \"from\": 4398, \"to\": 4421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Decisions on where, how and when to establish a rahui are made and managed by community leaders.\", \"from\": 4424, \"to\": 4520, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Decisions\", \"from\": 4424, \"to\": 4433}, {\"ngram\": \"a rahui\", \"from\": 4470, \"to\": 4477}, {\"ngram\": \"community leaders\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the years leading up to the 2019 establishment of the rahui in Teva I Uta, where Tehei lives, Tehei said he and other conservationists initially had a hard time convincing villagers that a rahui would be a good idea.\", \"from\": 4522, \"to\": 4741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4588, \"end\": 4598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teva_I_Uta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teva I Uta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teva_I_Uta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teva_I_Uta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 4525, \"to\": 4534}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2019 establishment\", \"from\": 4549, \"to\": 4571}, {\"ngram\": \"the rahui\", \"from\": 4575, \"to\": 4584}, {\"ngram\": \"Tehei\", \"from\": 4606, \"to\": 4611}, {\"ngram\": \"Tehei\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4624}, {\"ngram\": \"other conservationists\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4659}, {\"ngram\": \"a hard time\", \"from\": 4674, \"to\": 4685}, {\"ngram\": \"villagers\", \"from\": 4697, \"to\": 4706}, {\"ngram\": \"a rahui\", \"from\": 4712, \"to\": 4719}, {\"ngram\": \"a good idea\", \"from\": 4729, \"to\": 4740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Fishing is what provides resource money and food,\\\" said Tehei.\", \"from\": 4743, \"to\": 4806, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fishing\", \"from\": 4744, \"to\": 4751}, {\"ngram\": \"resource money\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4783}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 4788, \"to\": 4792}, {\"ngram\": \"Tehei\", \"from\": 4800, \"to\": 4805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They were afraid of not being able to access it when they were in the most need.\", \"from\": 4807, \"to\": 4888, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most need\", \"from\": 4874, \"to\": 4887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So of course they were a little nervous about that.\\\"\", \"from\": 4889, \"to\": 4941, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 4895, \"to\": 4901}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ruben, a fisherman, sets up his net in a lagoon outside of a marine reserve, or rahui, near Tautira, Tahiti.\", \"from\": 4943, \"to\": 5051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5035, \"end\": 5042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tautira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tautira\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tautira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tautira\"}, {\"begin\": 5044, \"end\": 5050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.999998344794227, \"rank\": 1.6552086216739654e-06, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ruben\", \"from\": 4